manifest_analysis.title:
Application Data can be Backed up
[android:allowBackup=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: This flag allows anyone to backup your application data via adb. It allows users who have enabled USB debugging to copy application data off of the device.
manifest_analysis.name: Application Data can be Backed up [android:allowBackup=true]

manifest_analysis.title:
Content Provider (com.mmbox.xbrowser.provider.BrowserProvider) would not be Protected if the application ran on a device where the the API level was less than 17.
[Content Provider, targetSdkVersion >= 17]
manifest_analysis.desc: The Content Provider( Content Provider) would be exported if the application ran on a device where the the API level was less than 17. In that situation, it would be shared with other apps on the device therefore leaving it accessible to any other application on the device.
manifest_analysis.name: would not be Protected if the application ran on a device where the the API level was less than 17.[Content Provider, targetSdkVersion >= 17]

manifest_analysis.title: Launch Mode of Activity (com.mmbox.xbrowser.BrowserActivity) is not standard.
manifest_analysis.desc: An Activity should not be having the launch mode attribute set to "singleTask/singleInstance" as it becomes root Activity and it is possible for other applications to read the contents of the calling Intent. So it is required to use the "standard" launch mode attribute when sensitive information is included in an Intent.
manifest_analysis.name: Launch Mode of Activity is not standard.

manifest_analysis.title:
Broadcast Receiver (com.mmbox.xbrowser.BrowserReceiver) is not Protected.
[android:exported=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: A Broadcast Receiver is found to be shared with other apps on the device therefore leaving it accessible to any other application on the device.
manifest_analysis.name: is not Protected. [android:exported=true]
